race.comment: MAALIS SONG (13) made it back-to-back wins last start when scoring by a half-length over this trip at Belmont. Now third-up, he looks set to peak with plenty of upside. Can land in a handy position from the barrier and continue his winning run. ROLLING RULER (12) looks an exciting horse on the way up. He flew late over 1000m at Ascot last start when 1.8L off the winner and the step back up to 1200m looks ideal now. Likely to be back from the draw but he's a classy type who can get back to winning ways. LADY BOSS (8) was a touch unlucky first-up when ducking back to the inside. May be able to take close order now with the run under her belt and Pike sticking is a good push. Can put her best foot forward. LET'S TALK (9) is unbeaten fresh and looks in good order judging by his recent trial. Can sit up front and be hard to run down. HELLUVA GODDESS (16) can fire a shot first-up.
